<HEAD>Wife Files for Divorce on Grounds That Husband Stinks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 28-year-old woman was justified in locking her
husband out of their apartment because he smelled, a judge ruled.
   ``There is no reason why the wife should be subjected to the
extremely uncomfortable situation,'' acting state Supreme Court
Justice Walter Schackman said in ruling this week.
   Jennifer Sheppard changed the locks on the couple's Manhattan
studio apartment Oct. 31 and told her husband, Darnay Hoffman, 41,
to stay away. She put his belongings in storage and filed for
divorce.
   In granting Sheppard sole possession of the apartment, Schackman
noted her contention that Hoffman had stopped washing his upper
body and wore the same clothes for weeks.
   Hoffman said the charges were untrue. ``I wasn't in the
apartment long enough to smell it up,'' he said.
   He said his wife was the source of the smell.
   Sheppard had no comment.
</TEXT>
