<BYLINE>Alberto Antignani</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alberto Antignani, superintendent of Rome's Theater
of the Opera since 1983, has died Monday at the age of 40.
   He died of an incurable illness, the family said. It gave no
details.
   Antignani became the youngest superintendent of Rome's most
important lyric theater when he was appointed to the post in May
1983 at age 35. He helped the theater survive a turbulent period of
financial difficulties, labor disputes and political squabbles.
