<FIRST>r i PM-PLO-Arafat     03-30 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-PLO-Arafat,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>Arafat Designated Head of Palestinian Government</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUNIS, Tunisia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The PLO's Executive Committee has
nominated Yasser Arafat to be president of the new independent
Palestinian state, a spokesman said today. Arafat is the only
candidate.
   Spokesman Ahmed Abderrahman said the nomination, made Tuesday,
will be submitted to the PLO's Central Committee for discussion and
possible action Friday.
   The meeting of the 70-member Central Committee serves as a sort
of mini-parliament session between regular meetings of the
Palestine National Council, the PLO's parliament-in-exile.
   The Palestinian council on Nov. 15 proclaimed a Palestinian
state and voted to name an exile government for the state, which
would include the Israel-occupied West Bank, east Jerusalem and the
Gaza Strip.
   Israel has refused to accept an independent Palestinian state
and rejects negotiations with the PLO, which it considers a
terrorist organization.
   As soon as Arafat's nomination is confirmed, he will
simultaneously fill the functions of president of the PLO Executive
Committee, commander-in-chief of Palestinian armed forces and
president of the independent state of Palestine.
