<FIRST>r i PM-Germany-Bush     03-30 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Germany-Bush,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bush Planning Brief West German Visit After May NATO Summit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush plans a short visit to
West Germany at the end of May after the 16-nation NATO summit in
Brussels, sources confirmed today.
   Speaking on condition of anonymity, the officials said Bush's
schedule had not yet been determined, but that he would hold
official visits and talks with Bonn officials on May 30 and 31.
   Bush will meet with West German Chancellor Helmut Kohl and the
other leaders of North Atlantic Treaty Organization nations during
the alliance summit in the Belgian capital on May 28-30.
   The trip is expected to be Bush's first European visit since he
took office as president in January.
   The last U.S. presidential visit to West Germany was in 1987,
when President Ronald Reagan stopped in Berlin after an economic
summit in Venice, Italy. He also visited Bonn and Bitburg during a
May 1985 visit.
</TEXT>
