<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Ecology     03-30 0172</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Ecology,0176</SECOND>
<HEAD>Group Plans Run to Draw Attention to Environmental Problems</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Environmentalists are sponsoring a 5,200-mile run
across China to highlight its ecological problems.
   About a dozen people from China and Japan have already signed up
for the May 1 run across the plateau of western China to its wooded
northeast, said Wang Gaoling, an organizer of the For Tomorrow, Run
Through China group. Some have signed up to run the whole distance,
while others will only run segments.
   Wang's group is made up of volunteers but has backing from the
Ministry of Forestry and China Central Television, he said.
   Wang said his group will also start a drive to raise funds for
the environmentally damaged areas of Beijing, Xian in the west and
Changchun in the northeast.
   In a related development, delegates at the ongoing session of
the National People's Congress, China's legislature, have proposed
the establishment of an environmental protection committee. China
already has an Environmental Protection Commission, which reports
to the State Council, or Cabinet.
</TEXT>
