<HEAD>New Defense Secretary Prefers `Dick,' not `Richard B.'</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Cheney Interview, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It's official. His name is Dick.
   Defense Secretary Dick Cheney discovered when he took office two
weeks ago that his office sign and memos bore the name Richard B.
Cheney.
   Throughout his political career, the ex-congreesman from Wyoming
had been Dick Chney. So reporters asked him Thursday how he wanted
his name to appear in print.
   ``I prefer Dick,'' he said with a laugh. ``I've always used
Dick. On the Hill, I always signed my letters that way. When I ran
for office, I always put Dick on the ballot.
   ``I was advised when I came down here that it's a little more
formal, that if you're going to sign an awfully lot of legally
required documents, which I do, then I ought to use Richard B.,''
he continued.
   ``They've had some trouble the first few days because stuff's
coming across my desk signed Richard B., but I'm still signing
Dick. I got a complaint about that the other day from staff. But
we'll get it straight here. But I prefer Dick.''
