<HEAD>Bush to Meet Four Family Members to Hear Their Concerns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush will meet Monday with four
family members of Americans killed when Pan Am Flight 103 exploded
over Lockerbie, Scotland, the White House said Thursday.
   Bush will ``hear their concerns,'' said Marlin Fitzwater, the
White House press secretary. The families are planning a memorial
service that afternoon in Lafayette Park, across the street from
the White House, he said.
   Fitzwater did not identify the four who will meet with Bush.
   The plane went down Dec. 21, killing all 259 people aboard and
another 11 on the ground.
   U.S. officials have denied knowledge of who was responsible for
the bombing.
   Investigators have confirmed a bomb caused the explosion. It was
contained in a radio-cassette player in the baggage hold.
   The plane had just left London's Heathrow Airport en route to
