<HEAD>Meeting Moved Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A meeting between President Bush and Jordan's
President King Hussein, originally scheduled for May 2, has been
moved up to April 19, White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater
announced Thursday.
   Bush will meet with three Middle Eastern leaders over the next
few weeks, including Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on Monday and
