<HEAD>More Envoys Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Thursday selected broadcast
executive Anthony Moore to be U.S. ambassador to Ireland.
   Since 1975, Moore has been associate producer for the McLaughlin
Group in Washington, D.C. He was a special counsel to the president
in the Nixon administration and is former chief executive officer
of the Times Mirror Broadcasting Co.
   If confirmed by the Senate, he would succeed Margarat M. Hechler.
   Bush had initially offered the post of U.S. ambassador to
Ireland to former House Speaker Thomas P. O'Neill, D-Mass., who
declined.
