cents a pound; feeder cattle were .05 cent to .35 cent lower with
April at 81.45 cents a pound; live hogs were .40 cent lower to .10
cent higher with April at 41.30 cents a pound; frozen pork bellies
were .27 cent to .55 cent lower with May at 38.05 cents a pound.
   Cattle futures settled higher on Wednesday while pork futures
finished mixed.
