<FIRST>r f AM-DairySupports     03-30 0140</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Dairy Supports,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Temporary Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Federal milk price supports will be
temporarily increased for three months beginning April 1 to $11.10
per 100 pounds from $10.60, Agriculture Secretary Clayton Yeutter
said Thursday.
   The increase was required by last year's Disaster Assistance
Act. Milk price supports are carried out by the Agriculture
Department's purchase of butter, cheese and non-fat dry milk to
bolster the market price of milk paid to farmers.
   Because of current market conditions, Yeutter said the
department's Commodity Credit Corp. will boost its purchase price
for non-fat dry milk to 79 cents per pound, an increase of 6.25
cents.
   The CCC's butter price will be unchanged at $1.32 per pound,
while the purchase price of cheddar and barrel cheese will be
increase by 5 cents per pound to slightly more than $1.20 per pound.
</TEXT>
