<HEAD>Midway Airlines Orders 29 Jets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Midway Airlines ordered 29 MD-82
mid-range airliners from McDonnell Douglas Corp., the manufacturer
announced Thursday.
   Combined with an earlier order of eight MD-87 planes, the value
of the Midway order is $900 million, Douglas said. The company
wouldn't reveal the value of just the new order.
   Midway also signed an agreement giving it the option to buy an
additional 37 of the twin-jet MD-82s, according to a statement from
Douglas Aircraft Co., a subsidiary of McDonnell Douglas Corp. of
St. Louis.
